        <!-- Modal -->
        <div class="modal fade" id="checkingModal" tabindex="-1" aria-labelledby="checkingModalLabel" aria-hidden="true">
            <div class="modal-dialog">
                <div class="modal-content">
                    <div class="modal-header">
                        <h5 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Checking Account</h5>
                        <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal" aria-label="Close">
                            <span aria-hidden="true">&times;</span>
                        </button>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-body">
                        <ul class="savingActList">
                            <li>Usually doesn't earn interest, but allows greater access to your money.</li>
                            <li>Use for money you spend day-to-day.</li>
                            <li>Use checks, ATM card, and/or debit card so you can use your money without using cash.</li>
                            <li>Overdraft: When there is not enough money in an account to cover a transaction and the bank pays it on your behalf, creating a negative balance in the account that you need to repay. Often results in a fee.</li>
                            <li>Some banks offer overdraft protection where the bank automatically transfers money from a linked account that you select, such as a savings or credit account, when you donâ€™t have enough money in your checking account to pay your transactions.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                    <div class="modal-footer">
                        <button type="button" class="btn btn-secondary" data-dismiss="modal" class='closebtn'>Close</button>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
